<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-07T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-07T03:35:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">741.9111/38: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-07T12:00:00+03:25">February
                                    7, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. Department’s 26, February 5.<note n="57" xml:id="d309fn57">Not
                                printed.</note> Immediately upon receipt Department’s 19, January
                                26,<note n="58" xml:id="d309fn58">See footnote 53, <ref target="#pg_268">p. 268</ref>.</note> I handed the Foreign
                            Minister a note which conveyed the reservation of rights and requested
                            the desired assurance. Foreign Minister promised early reply but stated
                            matter was technical and would require study. He added that while he did
                            not understand the points involved he was always glad to have an
                            expression of American interest in Iran’s problems.</p>
                        <p>Before delivering note I ascertained from British Minister that he had
                            informed Iranian Government of American participation along lines
                            suggested in Department’s 166, December 30.<note n="59" xml:id="d309fn59">
                                <ref target="frus1941v03#pg_485">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 485</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>